The headlight grills are starting to show some wear but still in very good condition.   This has the luggage rack on the rear with the twin grills over the engine lid, unique to the 356B.  The interior was red but now has an update tan interior.  The seats have no rips or tears, the door panels, carpet and the headliner are in great condition.  All the interior lights and guages are operational except for the clock. The car just had a tune-up with new ignition wires, spark plugs, ignition coil, condenser and points. description: Porsche produces precision machines designed for power, speed, handling, and head-turning. Porsches appeal broadly, yet desirability varies for different Porsche models. Art & Speed is pleased to present this carefully-restored, single-grille, D'Ieteren T5 roadster in red and ivory with a black cloth top.
